Jay Daley said:

@Mirja - the current GitHub process was designed after two public sessions at IETF meetings and with extensive input from some heavy GH users, who signed off on the design as suitable for integrating RPC edits in the RPC repo into the authors repo.

Yes, and these points came up over and over again. The process needs to work for both, the RPC and the authors. While we use this more widely, I hope we are still open for adaptation.
